# Super Queen Grand Finale

"Super Queen Grand Finale" is the tenth episode of the fourth season of the American television series ''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars''. It originally aired on February 15, 2019. Todrick Hall is a guest judge.
Episode
is a guest judge.]]
At the start of the episode, Monique Heart reveals that she would have sent home Latrice Royale from the competition had she won the lip-sync contest. For the final challenge of the season, the contestants write, record, and perform their own verses to RuPaul's song "Super Queen".
Todrick Hall is a guest judge. The runway category is All Star Eleganza. Monique Heart and Naomi Smalls are eliminated, leaving Monét X Change and Trinity the Tuck as the top two contestants of the season. They lip-sync to "Fighter" by Christina Aguilera. Monét X Change and Trinity the Tuck are both declared winners.
Production
The episode originally aired on February 15, 2019.
